            <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">ESI</ENAMEX> does not claim
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">infallibility</ENAMEX> or even the absence of silly mistakes, but we are not for sale.
We make the best case we can based on the facts as we know them. Moreover, we
do not attack <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">people</ENAMEX>, only ideas. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Krugman</ENAMEX> says "the currency of academic
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">success</ENAMEX> is creativity." Perhaps, but the ad hominem approach is usually the
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">mark</ENAMEX> of a weak argument.

