about eloquently--any economy-wide average will of course deviate increasingly
from the median, which much more accurately describes the situation of the
typical <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">worker</ENAMEX>.

            The
typical <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">worker</ENAMEX>'s situation can be more accurately gauged by looking at indexes
focusing on median figures for production, nonsupervisory <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">workers</ENAMEX>--who make up
